title: Infant mortality rate in the Netherlands 2008 to 2018
yAxis: Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children. In total the number of data points it has is 11.
In general Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children has fallen over the Year.
The most drastic decrease took place within the Year 2014 and 2015.
Maximum Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children, about 3.8 was reported at Year 2008,  2009,  2010, and 2013
Minimum Infant mortality per 1,000 live born children about 3.3 was reached at Year 2015
